abstract: Labor Dept reports initial claims for weekly unemployment benefits rose 1,000 to seasonally adjusted 295,000; reflects third consecutive weekly rise, though underlying metrics continue to indicate solid improvement in labor market.
lead_paragraph: Initial claims for state unemployment benefits increased 1,000 to a seasonally adjusted 295,000 for the week ended April 18, the Labor Department said.

headline.main: Jobless Claims Rise for 3rd Straight Week, but Labor Market Seems Stronger
headline.print_headline: Weekly Jobless Claims Rise, but Labor Market Still Shows Strength
